---
/* ReferenceDeskFooter (Site Update v9, Super-agent GAMMA, C.5).

   Persistent footer surface that lands above the existing footer-credit
   block on every page. Two named librarians — Margaret and Dave — with
   one-line role descriptions and a "How to ask the librarians" CTA.

   v9 ships text-only. Stylized portraits land in a follow-up commit when
   the Cowork-side ChatGPT generation produces them; the markup carries a
   `.reference-desk-footer__portraits` slot already-positioned for that
   drop-in.

   Mode behavior:
     - Library Mode (and Standard Mode): full surface, with a portrait
       slot to the left of each librarian once images arrive.
     - Reference Mode: the portrait slot is hidden via a scoped rule;
       the names and role lines remain (per the handoff: "rendered as
       plain text in Reference Mode").

   Class names are deliberately distinct from the existing
   `.reference-desk` component (homepage block) so this footer surface
   is not caught by mode-reference.css's `.reference-desk { display:
   none }` hide rule. The two surfaces are sibling expressions of the
   same idea, not the same DOM.
*/
---
<aside
  class="reference-desk-footer"
  aria-label="Library reference desk"
>
  <div class="reference-desk-footer__eyebrow">On the Reference Desk</div>
  <ul class="reference-desk-footer__list">
    <li class="reference-desk-footer__person">
      <div class="reference-desk-footer__portraits" aria-hidden="true">
        <span class="reference-desk-footer__portrait-placeholder">DS</span>
      </div>
      <div class="reference-desk-footer__body">
        <div class="reference-desk-footer__name">Dave Sullivan</div>
        <div class="reference-desk-footer__role">
          Founder. Lead advocate, OASTL. <a href="/about/how-this-works/#substrate">Knowledge Stack</a> architect.
        </div>
      </div>
    </li>
  </ul>
  <p class="reference-desk-footer__cta">
    <a href="/contribute/">How to ask the librarian &rarr;</a>
  </p>
</aside>

<style>
  .reference-desk-footer {
    max-width: 65ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.75rem;
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(216, 209, 194, 0.35);
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__eyebrow {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.18em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--old-gold, #B88A2E);
    margin-bottom: 0.85rem;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1.25rem 2rem;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__person {
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 0.85rem;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__portraits {
    flex: 0 0 auto;
    width: 3rem;
    height: 3rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    background: rgba(255, 253, 247, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(216, 209, 194, 0.4);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--old-gold, #B88A2E);
    line-height: 1;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__portrait-placeholder {
    user-select: none;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__body {
    flex: 1 1 auto;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__name {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: inherit;
    line-height: 1.25;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__role {
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.45;
    opacity: 0.9;
    margin-top: 0.15rem;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__cta {
    margin-top: 1.1rem;
    font-family: var(--font-sans);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 600;
  }

  .reference-desk-footer__cta a {
    color: var(--old-gold, #B88A2E);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* Reference Mode: text-only render, per the v9 handoff. The portrait
     slot drops; the surface keeps the names and role lines and the CTA.
     Astro scopes this selector automatically — only the portrait nodes
     inside this component are affected. */
  :global(body.mode-reference) .reference-desk-footer__portraits {
    display: none;
  }
  :global(body.mode-reference) .reference-desk-footer__person {
    gap: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .reference-desk-footer__list {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 1.25rem;
    }
  }
</style>
